Windows 7 Lost functionality
by Infidel » Wed 12.02.2009 8:06 pm I've been using the handwriting recognition tool for Windows Vista for a while now, and was very happy with it when writing Japanese. Recently I upgraded to Windows 7 and the Japanese handwriting recognition only works with Windows 7 Ultimate Edition now.It's very disappointing to pay for an upgrade and lose functionality. So this is a heads-up for anyone considering upgrading to Windows 7.
なるほど。
さっぱりわからん。
Infidel
